The paper deals with the task of computing relevance scores for knowledge-base triples, which is a problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed model integrates both latent and explicit features, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of a pre-trained embedding model and knowledge base extraction suggests the use of database systems (cs.DB).
